# Passwordless sudo for the kiosk account.
#
# Why: DebugBackend::runCommand() (shell-src/debugbackend.cpp) runs
# commands via QProcess with no controlling TTY. `sudo` can't prompt for
# a password in that context - it just fails immediately with "a
# terminal is required to read the password" instead of asking. Most of
# the useful wifi/touch/hardware diagnostics (rfkill, iw, dmesg, lspci,
# lsusb, udevadm) need root, so without this, half of commands.txt is
# unusable from the in-app Debug Console.
#
# Scope: full NOPASSWD, not a per-command allowlist. This matches the
# security posture already established for this account elsewhere (see
# 0100-setup-roohaniye.hook.chroot: "default password is intentionally
# simple/known... this account has no direct login prompt on a real
# boot"). roohaniye is not an admin/security boundary account - the
# app's own AuthBackend is the real user-facing lock (see continue.md).
# A per-command allowlist would also just break the next time a new
# diagnostic command is added to commands.txt or typed ad hoc into the
# console's free-text input field.
roohaniye ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD: ALL
